    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-04-28T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-04-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="741"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d741">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/23494.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Mediators</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Argentine Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-04-28">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 28, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mr. Secretary of State</hi>: It gives us satisfaction to
                    inform your excellency that we have received the acceptance of General Huerta’s
                    Government of our tender of good offices made through his excellency the
                    Ambassador of Spain.</p>
                <p>We are also glad to announce to your excellency that we made the same tender by
                    telegraph to the Chief of the Constitutionalist forces.<note n="20"
                        xml:id="d741fn20">See post, Inclosure 1 with the Special Commissioners’
                        despatch No. 8, May 31.</note>
                </p>
                <p>As a consequence of the acceptance of those good offices by your excellency’s
                    Government as well as by that of General Huerta, we <pb facs="0609" n="493"
                        xml:id="pg_493"/> understand that it is proper to suspend from this time,
                    and during the mediatory action, the hostilities and military movements by the
                    forces of both parties.</p>
                <p>We avail [etc.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <list>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">D. da Gama</hi>.</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">E. S. Naón</hi>.</item>
                            <item>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Ed’o Suárez Mujica</hi>
                            </item>
                        </list>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
